Wash and dry produce. Halve, peel, and thinly slice half the @red onion{1}(halved, peeled, and thinly sliced half); finely dice remaining half.

Zest one @lime{2}(zested and quartered), roughly chop @cilantro{1/4%ounce}(roughly chopped). Dice @tomato{2}(diced into 1/4-inch pieces). Halve, core, and chop half the @bell pepper{1}(halved, cored, and chopped half into 1/4-inch pieces) into 1/4-inch pieces. Drain @corn kernels{1}(drained). Drain and rinse @black beans{1}(drained and rinsed). Mince @jalapeño{1}(minced, ribs and seeds removed for less heat).

In a medium, microwave-safe #bowl{}, combine sliced onion, juice from one lime, and @sugar{1/2%tsp}. Microwave until onion is bright pink, ~{30%seconds}. Let cool slightly.

Stir in @shredded red cabbage{4%ounce}, half the @sour cream{4%tablespoon}, and half the cilantro; season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

In a #large bowl{}, combine tomatoes, diced onion, bell pepper, @rice wine vinegar{5%teaspoon}, half the corn, half the beans, remaining cilantro, @olive oil{2%tablespoon}, @Mexican spice blend{1%tablespoon}, juice from one lime, and as much jalapeño as you like. Taste and season with salt and pepper.

In a small bowl, combine @guacamole{4%tablespoon}, remaining sour cream, and half the lime zest. Season with salt and pepper.

Rinse @shrimp{10%ounce} under cold water, then pat dry with #paper towels{}. Season all over with remaining Mexican spice blend, salt, and pepper.

Heat a large drizzle of @cooking oil{2%teaspoon} in a #large pan{} over high heat. Once pan is hot, add shrimp and cook, stirring occasionally, until opaque and cooked through, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Remove pan from heat; add remaining lime zest and toss until shrimp are evenly coated.

Wrap @flour tortillas{6} in damp #paper towels{} and microwave until warm and pliable, ~{30%seconds}.

Divide tortillas between plates; fill with slaw and shrimp. Top tacos with creamy guacamole. Serve with @blue corn tortilla chips{3%ounce} and salsa on the side.

> Professional chef David knows a terrific taco comes down to the details: slaw tossed with pickled onion and cilantro, creamy guacamole with a hint of lime zest, and succulent shrimp seasoned with a curated blend of Mexican spices. These tacos also star a side of chunky salsa with tomato, corn, black beans, bell pepper, and jalapeño—perfect for dipping with blue corn tortilla chips. His husband Neil Patrick Harris gives this dish five stars, which can only mean one thing: When it comes to tacos, David knows best!